#Text=Libya and Switzerland to meet about visa bans
#Text=Thursday , February 18 , 2010

#Text=Libya
#Text=and Switzerland have reportedly agreed to meet in an effort to resolve a diplomatic row about travel visas .
#Text=Micheline Calmy-Rey
#Text=of Switzerland and Moussa Koussa of Libya will meet in the presence of Miguel Ángel Moratinos of Spain .
#Text=All three are the heads of foreign relations for their respective countries .
#Text=The meeting comes at the urging of Malta and Italy .
#Text=Libya announced on Tuesday that it has suspended and/or revoked visas given to citizens of the Schengen Area of Europe .
#Text=Four Italian citizens have been detained at the Tripoli International Airport pending deportation , as their visas have been revoked .
#Text=Confirming the situation , a Libyan official told Reuters : "

column1: #Text=Libya and Switzerland have been in a diplomatic row for many months .
#Text=In July 2008 , the Swiss for two days detained Libyan leader Muammar al-Gaddafi ' s son , Hannibal , after hotel staff in Geneva complained of being assaulted .
#Text=Hannibal was given a suspended sentence and released .
#Text=Since then , Libya has withdrawn more than US$ 5 billion ( € 3.6 billlion ) from Swiss banks and cut of oil exports to Switzerland .
#Text=Libya then detained two Swiss businessmen and sentenced one to 16 months of prison on visa violation charges .
#Text=In November , 2009 , Switzerland asked Schengen nations to restrict Libyan visas .
#Text=Subsequently , Libyan Prime Minister Baghdadi Mahmudi and other officials have been denied Schengen visas .
#Text=Italy
#Text=came down on Switzerland , saying the Swiss must " resolve this bi-lateral issue ... but not at the expense of everyone else .
